.TH "devcgroup_legacy_check_permission" 9 "devcgroup_legacy_check_permission" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devcgroup_legacy_check_permission \- checks if an inode operation is permitted
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" devcgroup_legacy_check_permission
.BI "(short type "  ","
.BI "u32 major "  ","
.BI "u32 minor "  ","
.BI "short access "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "type" 12
device type
.IP "major" 12
device major number
.IP "minor" 12
device minor number
.IP "access" 12
combination of DEVCG_ACC_WRITE, DEVCG_ACC_READ and DEVCG_ACC_MKNOD
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
returns 0 on success, -EPERM case the operation is not permitted
